#data

data <- read.csv("C:/Users/rakib/Desktop/Thesis/DATA/combined final data set/final_data.csv")

data <- data%>%
  select(-c(date, fips_code))

#data split and selected variables

#selected variables
selected_vars <- setdiff(names(data), c("total_outage", "county", 'event_name', 'open_water', 'shrub_and_herb_vegetation', 'forest_and_woodland', 'agricultural_and_developed_vegetation', 'min_rh'))
set.seed(1)
# Split data into 80% training and 20% testing
train_index <- createDataPartition(data$total_outage, p = 0.8, list = FALSE)
train_data <- data[train_index, ]
test_data <- data[-train_index, ]

#QRF

#Tune mtry with Cross-Validation
ctrl <- trainControl(method = "cv", number = 5, verboseIter = TRUE)

tune_grid <- expand.grid(
  mtry = c(4, 6, 8, 10, 12)
)
set.seed(1003)
tuned_qrf <- train(
  x = train_data[, selected_vars],
  y = train_data$total_outage,
  method = "qrf",
  tuneGrid = tune_grid,
  trControl = ctrl
)
## + Fold1: mtry= 4

## Selecting tuning parameters
## Fitting mtry = 12 on full training set
print(tuned_qrf)
## Quantile Random Forest 
## 
## 4636 samples
##   18 predictor
## 
## No pre-processing
## Resampling: Cross-Validated (5 fold) 
## Summary of sample sizes: 3709, 3709, 3709, 3708, 3709 
## Resampling results across tuning parameters:
## 
##   mtry  RMSE      Rsquared   MAE     
##    4    141414.0  0.7055784  14616.48
##    6    140968.9  0.6971758  14734.80
##    8    140249.3  0.6806625  14690.88
##   10    137979.4  0.6910023  14533.16
##   12    136074.7  0.7012126  14143.68
## 
## RMSE was used to select the optimal model using the smallest value.
## The final value used for the model was mtry = 12.
plot(tuned_qrf)

#variable imp
varImp(tuned_qrf, scale = FALSE)
## loess r-squared variable importance
## 
##                                 Overall
## prev_outage                   0.2472226
## mean_prcp                     0.0886550
## max_prcp                      0.0527378
## min_prcp                      0.0287958
## central_pressure              0.0240607
## avg_wind_speed_kts            0.0155165
## max_wind_gust_kts             0.0115639
## developed_and_other_human_use 0.0067687
## avg_rh                        0.0051392
## max_temp_f                    0.0031738
## density_mi2                   0.0024930
## day_difference                0.0024121
## max_rh                        0.0017901
## max_wind_speed_kts            0.0010126
## mean_min_ndvi                 0.0003544
## min_temp_f                    0.0001683
## mean_mean_ndvi                0.0001504
## prev_3day_avg_outage          0.0000000
plot(varImp(tuned_qrf, scale = FALSE))

#predict on test data
preds <- predict(tuned_qrf$finalModel, newdata = test_data[, selected_vars], what = c(0.10, 0.50, 0.90))
actuals <- test_data$total_outage
# Organize predictions
qrf_df <- data.frame(
  Actual = actuals,
  Q10 = preds[, 1],
  Q50 = preds[, 2],
  Q90 = preds[, 3]
)
qrf_df$Q10[qrf_df$Q5 < 0] <- 0
qrf_df$Q50[qrf_df$Q50 < 0] <- 0
qrf_df$Q90[qrf_df$Q95 < 0] <- 0
# Coverage
coverage <- mean(qrf_df$Actual >= qrf_df$Q10 & qrf_df$Actual <= qrf_df$Q90)
cat("Coverage (Q10Q90):", round(coverage * 100, 2), "%\n")
## Coverage (Q10Q90): 81.66 %
#evaluation
results <- postResample(pred = qrf_df$Q50, obs = actuals)
# Format results as a data frame
eval_table <- data.frame(
  Metric = c("RMSE", "R-squared", "MAE"),
  Value = c(
    round(results["RMSE"], 4),
    round(results["Rsquared"], 4),
    round(results["MAE"], 4)
  )
)

# Print table
print(eval_table)
##             Metric       Value
## RMSE          RMSE 102035.7348
## Rsquared R-squared      0.9237
## MAE            MAE  10633.9152
#Traditional/Definition based R2
sst <- sum((actuals - mean(actuals))^2)
sse <- sum((actuals - qrf_df$Q50)^2)
r2_traditional <- 1 - (sse / sst)
cat("Traditional R-squared:", round(r2_traditional, 4))
## Traditional R-squared: 0.8397
#Actual vs prediction plot
ideal_line_df <- data.frame(x = c(0, max(qrf_df$Actual)), y = c(0, max(qrf_df$Actual)))

ggplot(qrf_df, aes(x = Actual, y = Q50)) +
  geom_point(aes(color = "Actual vs Predicted Points"), alpha = 0.5) +
  geom_line(aes(color = "Median Line (Q50)"), size = 1) +
  geom_smooth(aes(color = "Regression Line"), method = "lm", se = FALSE) +
  geom_ribbon(aes(ymin = Q10, ymax = Q90, fill = "Prediction Interval"), alpha = 0.3) +

  # Ideal line as diagonal (in legend)
  geom_line(data = ideal_line_df, aes(x = x, y = y, color = "Ideal Line"), linetype = "dashed", size = 1) +

  scale_color_manual(
    name = "Line Legend",
    values = c(
      "Actual vs Predicted Points" = "blue",
      "Median Line (Q50)" = "green",
      "Regression Line" = "yellow",
      "Ideal Line" = "red"
    )
  ) +
  scale_fill_manual(
    name = "Interval Legend",
    values = c("Prediction Interval" = "gray")
  ) +
  scale_x_continuous(labels = scales::label_comma()) +
  scale_y_continuous(labels = scales::label_comma()) +
  labs(
    title = "Quantile Random Forest: Power Outage Prediction Intervals",
    x = "Actual Outage",
    y = "Predicted Median (Q50)"
  ) +
  theme_minimal()
## Warning: Using `size` aesthetic for lines was deprecated in ggplot2 3.4.0.

#variable imp

## loess r-squared variable importance
## 
##                                 Overall
## prev_outage                   0.5665383

## min_prcp                      0.0301579
## central_pressure              0.0268822
## avg_wind_speed_kts            0.0160381
## max_wind_gust_kts             0.0096536
## developed_and_other_human_use 0.0080627
## avg_rh                        0.0074491
## density_mi2                   0.0031930
## max_rh                        0.0029518
## max_temp_f                    0.0028154
## day_difference                0.0020802
## max_wind_speed_kts            0.0008341
## mean_mean_ndvi                0.0003731
## mean_min_ndvi                 0.0003728
## min_temp_f                    0.0001544
plot(varImp(tuned_qrf, scale = FALSE))

#predict on test data
preds <- predict(tuned_qrf$finalModel, newdata = test_data[, selected_vars], what = c(0.10, 0.50, 0.90))
actuals <- test_data$total_outage
# Organize predictions
qrf_df <- data.frame(
  Actual = actuals,
  Q10 = preds[, 1],
  Q50 = preds[, 2],
  Q90 = preds[, 3]
)
qrf_df$Q10[qrf_df$Q5 < 0] <- 0
qrf_df$Q50[qrf_df$Q50 < 0] <- 0
qrf_df$Q90[qrf_df$Q95 < 0] <- 0
# Coverage
coverage <- mean(qrf_df$Actual >= qrf_df$Q10 & qrf_df$Actual <= qrf_df$Q90)
cat("Coverage (Q10Q90):", round(coverage * 100, 2), "%\n")
## Coverage (Q10Q90): 84.36 %
#evaluation
results <- postResample(pred = qrf_df$Q50, obs = actuals)
# Format results as a data frame
eval_table <- data.frame(
  Metric = c("RMSE", "R-squared", "MAE"),
  Value = c(
    round(results["RMSE"], 4),
    round(results["Rsquared"], 4),
    round(results["MAE"], 4)
  )
)

# Print table
print(eval_table)
##             Metric     Value
## RMSE          RMSE 93736.349
## Rsquared R-squared     0.814
## MAE            MAE 11058.526
#Traditional/Definition based R2
sst <- sum((actuals - mean(actuals))^2)
sse <- sum((actuals - qrf_df$Q50)^2)
r2_traditional <- 1 - (sse / sst)
cat("Traditional R-squared:", round(r2_traditional, 4))
## Traditional R-squared: 0.7794
#Actual vs prediction plot
ideal_line_df <- data.frame(x = c(0, max(qrf_df$Actual)), y = c(0, max(qrf_df$Actual)))

ggplot(qrf_df, aes(x = Actual, y = Q50)) +
  geom_point(aes(color = "Actual vs Predicted Points"), alpha = 0.5) +
  geom_line(aes(color = "Median Line (Q50)"), size = 1) +
  geom_smooth(aes(color = "Regression Line"), method = "lm", se = FALSE) +
  geom_ribbon(aes(ymin = Q10, ymax = Q90, fill = "Prediction Interval"), alpha = 0.3) +

  # Ideal line as diagonal (in legend)
  geom_line(data = ideal_line_df, aes(x = x, y = y, color = "Ideal Line"), linetype = "dashed", size = 1) +

  scale_color_manual(
    name = "Line Legend",
    values = c(
      "Actual vs Predicted Points" = "blue",
      "Median Line (Q50)" = "green",
      "Regression Line" = "yellow",
      "Ideal Line" = "red"
    )
  ) +
  scale_fill_manual(
    name = "Interval Legend",
    values = c("Prediction Interval" = "gray")
  ) +
  scale_x_continuous(labels = scales::label_comma()) +
  scale_y_continuous(labels = scales::label_comma()) +
  labs(
    title = "Quantile Random Forest: Power Outage Prediction Intervals",
    x = "Actual Outage",
    y = "Predicted Median (Q50)"
  ) +
  theme_minimal()
## `geom_smooth()` using formula = 'y ~ x'

#predict on test data
preds <- predict(tuned_qrf$finalModel, newdata = test_data[, selected_vars], what = c(0.10, 0.50, 0.90))
actuals <- test_data$total_outage
# Organize predictions
qrf_df <- data.frame(
  Actual = actuals,
  Q10 = preds[, 1],
  Q50 = preds[, 2],
  Q90 = preds[, 3]
)
qrf_df$Q10[qrf_df$Q5 < 0] <- 0
qrf_df$Q50[qrf_df$Q50 < 0] <- 0
qrf_df$Q90[qrf_df$Q95 < 0] <- 0
# Coverage
coverage <- mean(qrf_df$Actual >= qrf_df$Q10 & qrf_df$Actual <= qrf_df$Q90)
cat("Coverage (Q10Q90):", round(coverage * 100, 2), "%\n")
## Coverage (Q10Q90): 81.52 %
#evaluation
results <- postResample(pred = qrf_df$Q50, obs = actuals)
# Format results as a data frame
eval_table <- data.frame(
  Metric = c("RMSE", "R-squared", "MAE"),
  Value = c(
    round(results["RMSE"], 4),
    round(results["Rsquared"], 4),
    round(results["MAE"], 4)
  )
)

# Print table
print(eval_table)
##             Metric     Value
## RMSE          RMSE 4657.1448
## Rsquared R-squared    0.1505
## MAE            MAE 1439.1581
#Traditional/Definition based R2
sst <- sum((actuals - mean(actuals))^2)
sse <- sum((actuals - qrf_df$Q50)^2)
r2_traditional <- 1 - (sse / sst)
cat("Traditional R-squared:", round(r2_traditional, 4))
## Traditional R-squared: 0.1153
#Actual vs prediction plot
ideal_line_df <- data.frame(x = c(0, max(qrf_df$Actual)), y = c(0, max(qrf_df$Actual)))

ggplot(qrf_df, aes(x = Actual, y = Q50)) +
  geom_point(aes(color = "Actual vs Predicted Points"), alpha = 0.5) +
  geom_line(aes(color = "Median Line (Q50)"), size = 1) +
  geom_smooth(aes(color = "Regression Line"), method = "lm", se = FALSE) +
  geom_ribbon(aes(ymin = Q10, ymax = Q90, fill = "Prediction Interval"), alpha = 0.3) +

  # Ideal line as diagonal (in legend)
  geom_line(data = ideal_line_df, aes(x = x, y = y, color = "Ideal Line"), linetype = "dashed", size = 1) +

  scale_color_manual(
    name = "Line Legend",
    values = c(
      "Actual vs Predicted Points" = "blue",
      "Median Line (Q50)" = "green",
      "Regression Line" = "yellow",
      "Ideal Line" = "red"
    )
  ) +
  scale_fill_manual(
    name = "Interval Legend",
    values = c("Prediction Interval" = "gray")
  ) +
  scale_x_continuous(labels = scales::label_comma()) +
  scale_y_continuous(labels = scales::label_comma()) +
  labs(
    title = "Quantile Random Forest: Power Outage Prediction Intervals",
    x = "Actual Outage",
    y = "Predicted Median (Q50)"
  ) +
  theme_minimal()
## `geom_smooth()` using formula = 'y ~ x'
